          "body": "Twice in the chapter the verb shifts: 'Israel *lived* (yashab) in all the cities of the Amorites' (21:25), and 'Thus Israel *dwelt* in the land of the Amorites' (21:31). Both clauses are pregnant. For 40 years Israel has only camped (chanah, the verb of 21:10-13). Now, for the first time since Egypt, they *dwell*. The wilderness vocabulary gives way to inheritance vocabulary. The chapter is, in this sense, the beginning of the end of the wandering — the proleptic taste of the Sabbath rest that Joshua will largely secure and that, ultimately, Hebrews 4 says still awaits the people of God. Numbers 21 inaugurates the pattern: the look of faith (v. 9) is what brings the wandering to its rest."
